notesStmt.note: Considerably stained and blurred in parts.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Genesis and Exodus, with simple superlinear punctuation and accents.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 17; written lines: 17; Visible pricking; ruling executed with hard-point. Writing in one column, with superlinear masoretic punctuation.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Square Yemenite scrupt of about 15th century.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Museum from him on 23 July 1881: inscribed, [119v] .
